CIE Four-Wheeled Bulk Cement Wagons were known as &quot;bubbles&quot;
<a href="http://newirishlines.org/2009/03/06/cie-four-wheeled-bulk-cement-wagons/" rel="nofollow">newirishlines.org/2009/03/06/cie-four-wheeled-bulk-cement...</a>
Us old folk never used the phrase &quot;Train Station&quot;, always &quot;Railway Station&quot;.

From the article, these wagons carried dry cement powder, not premixed concrete.
&quot;<i>Fluidised bed</i> is common in industry to make a heavy mass of powder behave like a fluid by pumping high pressure air through it.&quot;
From old Pete in Blackpool, age 70&#189;
